import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
In [ ]:
sorts = [
    "selection",
    "bubble",
    "bubble-iverson-1",
    "bubble-iverson-2",
    "insertion",
    "bin-insertion",
    "counting",
    "radix",
    "merge",
    "quick",
    "heap",
    "shell-ciura",
    "shell"
]

arrays = [
    "small-range",
    "big-range",
    "almost-sorted",
    "reversed"
]
In [ ]:
data = pd.read_csv('../data/ops-large.csv', sep=';', header=None)
data.columns = ['sort', 'array', 'size', 'ops']
In [ ]:
def print_sort(data, sort):
    sort_df = data[data['sort'] == sort]
    plt.figure(figsize=(20, 20))
    for array in arrays:
        df = sort_df[sort_df['array'] == array]
        plt.plot(df['size'], df['ops'], label=array)
    plt.title(sort)
    plt.xlabel('Array Size')
    plt.xticks(sort_df['size'].unique())
    plt.ylabel('Operations count')
    plt.legend(labelcolor='black', prop={'size': 15})
In [ ]:
def print_array(data, array):
    array_df = data[data['array'] == array]
    plt.figure(figsize=(20, 20))
    for sort in sorts:
        df = array_df[array_df['sort'] == sort]
        plt.plot(df['size'], df['ops'], label=sort)
    plt.title(array)
    plt.xlabel('Array Size')
    plt.xticks(array_df['size'].unique())
    plt.ylabel('Operations count')
    plt.legend(labelcolor='black', prop={'size': 15})
